{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Quantum Capstone Project: Introduction to Grover's Algorithm\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook provides a step-by-step walkthrough of Grover's search algorithm.\n",
    "\n",
    "## What You Will Learn\n",
    "1. How quantum superposition enables parallel search\n",
    "2. How the oracle marks solutions with phase flips\n",
    "3. How the diffusion operator amplifies solutions\n",
    "4. How to implement this in Qiskit 2.0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "First, let's import the necessary libraries:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Core quantum computing library\n",
    "from qiskit import QuantumCircuit\n",
    "from qiskit.quantum_info import Statevector\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization import plot_histogram, plot_bloch_multivector\n",
    "\n",
    "# Numerical computing\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Our custom modules (adjust path as needed)\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append('../src')\n",
    "\n",
    "from grover import two_qubit_grover_11, four_qubit_grover\n",
    "from gates import apply_hadamard_all, apply_oracle_marker, apply_diffusion_operator\n",
    "from utils import print_statevector_probabilities\n",
    "\n",
    "print("Libraries imported successfully!")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 1: Understanding Superposition\n",
    "\n",
    "The Hadamard gate creates superposition - the quantum property that allows parallel computation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create a single qubit in superposition\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply Hadamard gate\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize the circuit\n",
    "print("Circuit:")\n",
    "print(qc.draw(output='text'))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the quantum state\n",
    "state = Statevector.from_instruction(qc)\n",
    "print(f"\nStatevector: {state.data}")\n",
    "print(f"|0> probability: {abs(state.data[0])**2:.1%}")\n",
    "print(f"|1> probability: {abs(state.data[1])**2:.1%}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 2: Multi-Qubit Superposition\n",
    "\n",
    "With 2 qubits, we get 4 states simultaneously:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create 2-qubit superposition\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.h([0, 1])\n",
    "\n",
    "state = Statevector.from_instruction(qc)\n",
    "print("2-qubit uniform superposition:")\n",
    "for i in range(4):\n",
    "    bits = format(i, '02b')\n",
    "    prob = abs(state.data[i])**2\n",
    "    print(f"  |{bits}>: {prob:.1%}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 3: The Oracle - Marking Solutions\n",
    "\n",
    "The oracle applies a phase flip (-1) to the solution state. This doesn't change probabilities yet, but changes the phase."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create circuit and put in superposition\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.h([0, 1])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply oracle (CZ tags |11>)\n",
    "qc.cz(0, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "state = Statevector.from_instruction(qc)\n",
    "print("After oracle (solution |11> tagged):\n")\n",
    "for i in range(4):\n",
    "    bits = format(i, '02b')\n",
    "    amp = state.data[i]\n",
    "    print(f"  |{bits}>: {amp.real:+.3f} {amp.imag:+.3f}i")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 4: The Diffusion Operator - Amplifying Solutions\n",
    "\n",
    "The diffusion operator reflects amplitudes about the average, amplifying the tagged solution."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Complete 2-qubit Grover circuit\n",
    "qc = two_qubit_grover_11()\n",
    "\n",
    "print("Complete 2-qubit Grover circuit:")\n",
    "print(qc.draw(output='text'))\n",
    "\n",
    "state = Statevector.from_instruction(qc)\n",
    "print("\nFinal probabilities:")\n",
    "print_statevector_probabilities(state.data, highlight_index=3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 5: Scaling to 4 Qubits\n",
    "\n",
    "With 4 qubits, we can search through 16 states. The algorithm uses 3 iterations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Build 4-qubit circuit\n",
    "solution = "0010"\n",
    "qc = four_qubit_grover(solution)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"4-qubit Grover circuit for |{solution}>")\n",
    "print(f"Number of gates: {len(qc.data)}\n")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run simulation\n",
    "state = Statevector.from_instruction(qc)\n",
    "probs = abs(state.data)**2\n",
    "\n",
    "# Find solution index (Qiskit LSB ordering)\n",
    "solution_idx = int(solution[::-1], 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"Solution |{solution}> is at index {solution_idx}")\n",
    "print(f"Solution probability: {probs[solution_idx]*100:.1f}%\n")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show top 5 states\n",
    "print("Top 5 most probable states:")\n",
    "for idx in np.argsort(probs)[-5:][::-1]:\n",
    "    bits = format(idx, '04b')\n",
    "    marker = " <- SOLUTION" if idx == solution_idx else ""\n",
    "    print(f"  |{bits}>: {probs[idx]*100:6.2f}%{marker}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 6: Visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's visualize the probability distribution:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create bar chart of probabilities\n",
    "labels = [format(i, '04b') for i in range(16)]\n",
    "values = probs\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "colors = ['red' if i == solution_idx else 'blue' for i in range(16)]\n",
    "plt.bar(labels, values, color=colors)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('State')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Probability')\n",
    "plt.title(f"Grover\'s Algorithm: Solution |{solution}>")\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Exercises\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Try different 4-bit solutions and observe the probabilities\n",
    "2. What happens if you use only 2 iterations instead of 3?\n",
    "3. What happens with 4 iterations? (Hint: you overshoot!)\n",
    "4. Can you implement a 3-qubit version?"
   ]
  }
 ],
